AWARD-WINNING house music producer Heavy K is allegedly officially off the market!It is rumoured &ldquo;Heavy K&rdquo;, real name Mkhululi Siqula, couldn&rsquo;t hide his excitement after allegedly getting engaged to his girlfriend, Innocentia Morolong. The producer, who is popularly known as the &ldquo;Drumboss&rdquo;, posted a picture on social media with the caption: I liked it &amp; then putted (sic) a ring on it.A source close to the couple said the proposal was long overdue.&ldquo;They started dating last year and since then, they&rsquo;ve been all over each other. They&rsquo;ve tried to keep their love life out of the spotlight, but it&rsquo;s hard as they&rsquo;re inseparable,&rdquo; said the source.The source said when Heavy K bought Innocentiahis new fiancee a car, it was clear the ring was next on the list.Another source said Heavy K worships the ground Innocentia walks on.Said the source: &ldquo;He hasn&rsquo;t been the same since they met and has hinted she&rsquo;s the woman he&rsquo;d spend the rest of his life with.&rdquo;Last year Sunday Sun reported they were lovers, but the couple denied it.When called for comment, Innocentia couldn&rsquo;t confirm or deny she was engaged.She said: &ldquo;That&rsquo;s a thing I can&rsquo;t comment on. Not in the bad way, I prefer not to talk about my love life.&rdquo;Heavy-K asked the SunTeam to send him an email, but he hadn&rsquo;t replied at the time of going to press.